725154f-a.text:
27th Avenue, north side, between 8th and 9th Streets, showing the Joseph Blackwell house of 1873. Joseph Blackwell was a dry goods merchant in New York City. The house is set back about 150 feet from the normal building line. Subsequent
to 1929 it was used as a multiple dwelling.

View 1:  Eugene L. Armbruster  1922

View 2:  P.L. Sperr  March 11, 1931

View 3:  George D. Chinn  April 27, 1940
